verbose_text: However the post-translational modifications of the collagen were markedly different between OA-prone DH and non prone BS2 strains, with significantly lower levels of lysyl hydroxylation and higher levels of the cross-link L-Pyr, associated with a mineralising matrix, in the DH strain [P = 0.01 and P < 0.0001 respectively; XREF_FIG (A and B)].
evidence: levels of lysyl hydroxylation and higher levels of the cross-link L-Pyr
